         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne bot Garden  ¶ 1/12/70. ¶  ¶ It may interest you to know, dear Mr Bentham, that a true Ilex has been found in N.E. Australia, allied to Ilex Wightiana. I called it I. pedunculosa. ¶  A new ge...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">70.12.01</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To George Bentham</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1858-70, f. 453.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne bot Garden </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">1/12/70.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It may interest you to know, dear Mr Bentham, that a true Ilex has been found in N.E. Australia, allied to <name key="Ilex%20Wightiana">Ilex Wightiana</name>. I called it I. pedunculosa.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Described as <seg style="font-style: italic; ">I. peduncularis</seg> in B70.12.03, p. 105.</p>
               </note> A new genus of <name key="Araliaceae">Araliaceae</name> has also just turned up, belonging to the true Araliac[eous] section. I named it <name key="Motherwellia">Motherwellia</name>.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M erected <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Motherwellia">Motherwellia</name>
                     </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">(M.</seg>
                     <seg style="font-size: 12pt; font-style: italic; font-weight: bold; "> </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">haplosciadea</seg>) in B70.12.03, p. 107.</p>
               </note> After much anxieties in the Department, which indeed still continue, I have managed (though under real distractions) to finish a new number of the Fragmenta. It contains among other curious things a monostachyous <name key="Chloris">Chloris</name>.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Chloris">Chloris</name> unispicea</seg>, B70.12.03, p. 118.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Trusting you are well </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I remain your regardful</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">The copies of the 5th volume<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Bentham (1863-78), vol. 5.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> did safely arrive.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have settled the boundaries of many <name key="Haemodoraceae">Haemodoraceae</name> also more accurately then was known before.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Araliaceae">Araliaceae</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Chloris">Chloris</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Haemodoraceae">Haemodoraceae</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Ilex%20pedunculosa">Ilex pedunculosa</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Ilex%20Wightiana">Ilex Wightiana</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Motherwellia">Motherwellia</name>
            </p>
         </div>
